HEADWORD: Polygenist
<hw>Po*lyg"e*nist</hw> <pr>(-n⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>One who maintains that animals of the same
species have sprung from more than one original pair; -- opposed to
<contr>monogenist</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polygenous</ent>⟦br⟧
